PPE Sales Executive
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/04/30 15:40:45
Ref. JB3045926
Job Description
Products – Fire & Gas Detection, Fire Fighting & Safety Equipments
• Analyzing the requirement of the client and short listing of approved Suppliers/ Vendors.
• Obtaining quotations and negotiation for the best price.
• Evaluating, pricing and preparing the Techno-commercial Bids/ Quotations for clients.
• Follow up on Quotations submitted & Clarifying the Client Queries.
• Coordination of Logistics. (Air / Sea / Land)
• Coordinating with our warehouse & ensuring timely delivery.
• Coordination of warranty claims and service requests.
• Ensuring of Timely Invoicing & Payment follow up, if required.
• Demonstrate the products to clients and take orders.
• Update knowledge on similar products & explain to customers which product is worth buying for them.
• Suggest the products according to customer need and budget.
• Attend customer queries & redress their grievances.
• Provide after sales support to customers and the company.
• Closely monitor the market trend and inform the management accordingly.
• Accounts entries and maintaining all records.
• Preparing Balance Sheet for Auditing.
• Co-ordinate with the management in all day-to-day assignments.
• Responsible for the business development of AL USOOL in PPE.
• Established strong relationship with local and International business partners.
• Created and implemented account development strategies that significantly enhanced growth.
• Responsible for handling ON GOING CONTRACTS with POTENTIAL CLIENTS in the Oil & Gas Industry.
• Actively contribute to achieve sales targets through increase profit margins.
• Research & develop new sources from around the globe to meet the competition & sustain the business.
• Knowledge of current market conditions, pricing & sources of supply and services.
• Work closely with all levels of management within the Company to determine needs, develop strategies and plan and provide business solutions.
• Solicit bids; secure written and telephone quotations from Principal partners.
• Analyze bids, perform value and cost analysis and select products and Principal Partners consistent with existing policies and procedures and assist other staff members in doing the same.
• Monitor order and contracts for compliance and performance.
• Initiating and sustaining long term price agreements with end users.
• Co-ordination with the logistics team to ensure delivery timeliness.
• Communicate clearly, concisely and courteously, orally and in writing, and maintain effective business relationships with other employees, vendors, Principal Partners and clients.
• Establishing, maintaining and sustaining key accounts of oil and gas industry.
• Sourcing and finding potential business partners/vendors and managing all transactions and business dealings.
• To create sales strategy and create new distributors and end-users and also support existing distributors& sub- distributors customers.
• Prepare quotation to supplier before placing an order.
• Check order confirmation against purchase order regarding ordered goods, prices and date of delivery.
• Assist to Finance manager in the credit control system
• Do presentations with end-users.
• Conduct daily assessment, planning, and implementation on the Customer feedbacks and follow-ups.
• Maintain stock records and conduct offer for stock clean projects & campaigns.
•
Additional Responsibilities Entrusted:
• Making client visits for Agency Product Promotion.
• Maintaining/ Monitoring the ISO 9001:2008 procedures within the work place.
• Handling the team and diving the IRAQI region into the sales representative.
• Having a full knowledge of the differences between all international brands around the world.
• Developing from A to Z PPE department for UGT.
Skills
• Good at negotiations.
• Computer Skills - MS Office, Photoshop.
• Good command over Language – English and Arabic.
• Patient.
• Hard worker.
• Focused.
• Quick Learner.
• Work Oriented.
